<item>
            <title>[CASSANDRA-5072] Bug in creating EnumSet in SimpleAuthorizer example</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CASSANDRA-5072</link>
                <project id="12310865" key="CASSANDRA">Apache Cassandra</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;In SimpleAuthorizer around line 47 we have,&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;EnumSet&amp;lt;Permission&amp;gt; authorized = EnumSet.copyOf(Permission.NONE);&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;This results in an IllegalArgumentException since Permission.NONE is an empty set. I think it should be changed to,&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;EnumSet&amp;lt;Permission&amp;gt; authorized = EnumSet.noneOf(Permission.class);&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
        <key id="12624114">CASSANDRA-5072</key>
            <summary>Bug in creating EnumSet in SimpleAuthorizer example</summary>
                <type id="1" iconUrl="https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/viewavatar?size=xsmall&amp;avatarId=21133&amp;avatarType=issuetype">Bug</type>
